# Monorepo Commands

## Backend (Java/Vert.x)

```bash
cd backend/server && mvn clean install        # build + test
cd backend/server && mvn verify               # tests + checkstyle
```

## Frontend (React/TypeScript)

```bash
cd pulse-ui && yarn install && yarn start     # dev server on :3000
cd pulse-ui && yarn build                     # production build
cd pulse-ui && yarn lint                      # ESLint
```

## AI Agent (Python/Google ADK — Docker)

```bash
cd pulse_ai && cp .env.example .env           # first time — set GOOGLE_API_KEY
cd pulse_ai && ./setup.sh                     # build + start (Docker, port 8000)
cd pulse_ai && ./setup.sh logs                # tail logs
cd pulse_ai && ./setup.sh stop                # stop
```

## Docker (full stack)

```bash
cd deploy && ./scripts/quickstart.sh          # build + start all
cd deploy && ./scripts/build.sh [ui|server|cron|all]
cd deploy && ./scripts/start.sh [-d|--detach] [--build]
cd deploy && ./scripts/stop.sh [-v]
cd deploy && ./scripts/logs.sh [service]
```

To discover running services and their actual ports:
```bash
docker ps --format "table {{.Names}}\t{{.Ports}}\t{{.Status}}"
```

## Key Ports

| Service | Port | Health |
|---------|------|--------|
| pulse-server | 8080 | `/healthcheck` |
| pulse-ui | 3000 | `/healthcheck.txt` |
| pulse-ai (Docker) | 8000 | `curl http://localhost:8000` |
| alerts-cron | 4000 | `/healthcheck` |
| ClickHouse | 8123 (HTTP), 9000 (native) | `SELECT 1` |
| MySQL | 3307 | `mysqladmin ping` |
| OpenFGA | 8180 (HTTP), 8181 (gRPC), 3001 (playground) | `/healthz` |
| OTEL Collector | 4317/4318, 13133 (health) | — |

## Never commit `.env` files. Use `.env.example` as template.
